      "source": [
        "2.   **Enhancing Accuracy Through Code Optimization**\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "In the provided code snippet, I made several adjustments to improve the model's training process and overall performance. Firstly, I imported the EarlyStopping and LearningRateScheduler callbacks from tensorflow.keras.callbacks, which are essential for implementing early stopping and learning rate scheduling functionalities during model training. Next, I created instances of these callbacks with specific settings: EarlyStopping was configured to monitor the validation loss and halt training if no improvement occurred for 3 consecutive epochs, while LearningRateScheduler was defined as a function to dynamically adjust the learning rate based on the current epoch number. Specifically, the learning rate was reduced by a factor of 0.1 every 5 epochs to facilitate better convergence. Finally, I included these callbacks in the fit() method call using the callbacks argument to ensure their utilization throughout the training process, thereby enhancing the model's stability and performance."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CXlxReOHoFEA"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping, LearningRateScheduler"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "X8wQveN9jjs7"
      },
      "execution_count": 14,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "image_height = 64\n",
        "image_width = 28\n",
        "# Define model architecture with adjusted input shape\n",
        "model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(28, 28, 1)),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2)),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Flatten(),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dropout(0.5),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Compile the model with Adam optimizer and learning rate of 0.001\n",
        "model.compile(\n",
        "    optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=0.001),  # Changed\n",
        "    loss=tf.keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(from_logits=True),\n",
        "    metrics=[tf.keras.metrics.SparseCategoricalAccuracy()]\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Define EarlyStopping and LearningRateScheduler callbacks\n",
        "early_stopping = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=3, restore_best_weights=True)\n",
        "def lr_scheduler(epoch, lr):\n",
        "    if epoch % 5 == 0:\n",
        "        return lr * 0.1\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        return lr\n",
        "lr_scheduler_callback = LearningRateScheduler(lr_scheduler)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train the model with callbacks\n",
        "history = model.fit(\n",
        "    train_data,\n",
        "    epochs=20,\n",
        "    validation_data=test_data,\n",
        "    callbacks=[early_stopping, lr_scheduler_callback]  # Changed\n",
        ")"
      ],
